A BGe Score for Tied-Covariance Mixture Gaussian Bayesian Networks

This GitHub repository contains the R code accompanying the paper

"A BGe Score for Tied-Covariance Mixture Gaussian Bayesian Networks"

published in the International Journal of Approximate Reasoning (2026)

A link to the published paper will be added once it becomes available.

Author: Marco Grzegorczyk

Affiliation: Bernoulli Institute, University of Groningen, The Netherlands

Email: m.a.grzegorczyk@rug.nl

The file WORKED_EXAMPLE.R provides a step-by-step demonstration of the method. 
The R commands can be executed line by line.
